However, if products of three symmetric matrices are considered, any permutation is allowed. (Proof: tr("ABC") = tr("A"T "B"T "C"T) = tr("A"T("CB")T) = tr(("CB")T"A"T) = tr(("ACB")T) = tr("ACB"), where the last equality is because the traces of a matrix and its transpose are equal.) For more than three factors this is not true.
Unlike the determinant, the trace of the product is not the product of traces. What is true is that the trace of the tensor product of two matrices is the product of their traces:
